latestIgtvVideos.caption:
𝙘𝙝𝙚𝙚𝙨𝙚 𝘽𝙪𝙣𝙙𝙩 𝘾𝙖𝙠𝙚 🤎❤️

Recipe
1 1/2 cups self rising flour 
1/2 cup white sugar
1 cup brown sugar
3/4 cup cocoa powder
1/2 cup sour cream
200gm butter
300gm chocolate 
1 tbsp vanilla essence 
3 eggs

Cream cheese filling 
16 oz cream cheese 
1/2 cup sugar 
1 egg
2 tsp vanilla essence 

Chocolate Ganache 
1 cup semi sweet chocolate 
3/4 cup heavy whipping cream
1 tbsp butter 

Method 
Preheat the oven 170 C
Melt the chocolate and butter 
Sift the dry ingredients 
In a large bowl mix brown and white sugar 
Add 3 beaten eggs, vanilla essence, add the melted chocolate and sour cream. 
Whisk until well combined.
Add the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients and gently fold in.

For cream cheese layer-
Beat the cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla essence together until smooth and creamy.

Keep your cherry compote ready. 

Layer the Bundt cake with brownie batter,cheese layer, cherry compote and complete with brownie batter .
 
Bake for 55 to 60 mints

Prepare the ganache and Glaze the cake with chocolate ganache or cherry compote or add both and enjoy 😋

This is truly an irresistible cake ever 👌🏻

latestIgtvVideos.title: Kunefe / Kunafa / kunafeh - A middle eastern pastry dessert 💕🧡🌙💚💕
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Recipe :
Cheese: 
Akawai 400gm ( u can use halloumi or ricotta too ) 
Mozzarella 200gm 
Thick cream 

If using Akawai cheese make sure to cut into cubes and soak in water and refrigerate for 4 to 6 hrs. By changing the water every 2hrs . 
Strain n set aside . 

1st prepare the syrup :
1 & 1/2 cup sugar 
1 cup water 
1/2 tsp lemon juice 
Cinnamon stick 
Rose petals 

Add everything to a pan over a medium to high heat let it cook for 10 mints or until sugar is dissolved, give it a stir and set aside . ( do not cook more as the syrup will thicken) 

 Knafeh 
500 gm Kanfeh dough ( frozen) 
Ghee 1/2 cup 
Butter 4 tbsp 
orange food color 

2nd- For the knafeh, take the dough (katayif pastry) and pull apart/ shred so the strands are separated. cut the dough so that the strands are shorter. Shred the dough add ghee and combine well. 

3rd -Now add the butter , orange color n mix well. Grease the pan . It’s gives a beautiful color . 

4th -Add half the knafeh dough to the pan. Press down firmly using hands or glass . 

5th- Add the strained akawai cheese, mozzarella cheese leaving the sides about an inch .so that the cheese doesn't ooze out. Add the cream . Add the remaining pastry to cover the cheese and press down gently. 

Bake in a pre-heated oven of 200 C 
For 20 to 30 mints or until the top is golden brown. 

Remove from the oven . Cover and keep aside for 2 to 3 mints. Invert to a serving plate and drizzle the syrup . Garnish with crushed pistachios and rose petals and Serve hot for melting and stringy cheese. 

Before serving drizzle some more syrup and enjoy !

latestIgtvVideos.title: Chicken Mandi 👩🏻‍🍳
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Friday Special Chicken Mandi for Dinner after Iftaar or for  Suhoor . 

Iftaar Day 25 - 

Mandi is a mixed rice dish served on a communal platter , and originated from Yemen 🇾🇪 

The dish is made of rice and slow cooked mea, where the meat & rice is cooked separately with the special blend of spices .Then the chicken or meat is served on a bed of steaming rice along with zahawiq sauce ( spicy salsa or chutney) . 

I added a little bit of twist where I used the chicken broth for cooking the rice , similar to Kabsa and Kabsa is a National dish of Saudi Arabia which 
Also known as Makbus/ machbus. 

It’s such a delicious feast 😋👌🏻 
Turned out so good 🔥 made it today to make it special as it’s the last Friday of Ramadan for this year . 

Here is a video of making this delicious Mandi and Zahawiq sauce .
